**Manual paste — ask the user if they have any of these:**
- **Pendo** — paste the URL of a relevant insight or a CSV/text export of the funnel or feature usage you want context on.
- **Mixpanel** — paste a report URL or exported CSV/JSON for the relevant chart.
- **Dovetail / user-interview summaries** — paste the doc link or the relevant excerpt.
- **Mobbin / Land-book / Dribbble / Page-flows** — paste reference URLs for similar designs you want analyzed.

If the user provides these, integrate them into the brief. If not, name the missing context explicitly so downstream phases know the limitation.

## Hand-off

When done, summarize the brief in one paragraph and recommend the next phase:
- `designer-spec-writer` — you have enough to write a spec.
- More research — name the specific gaps that need closing first.

## Project context (auto-tune)

Before doing any work, read context for the *current* project (not generation-time):
- `~/.claude/projects/<flatten(cwd)>/memory/*.md` — project rules
- `~/.agents/skills/auto-tune/cache/corrections.json` — recent correction patterns
- `~/.claude/.role` or `<cwd>/.claude/.role` — role for this session

`flatten(cwd)` = leading `/` stripped, then replace `[/.,\s]` with `-`, then prepend `-`. Apply rules that match the current cwd. If memory is empty, skip silently.
